          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A deuterated  (C(D-2))  and  an   ordinary   (C(H-2))",
                " polyethelene  targets  were  used.  the targets were",
                " pressed from polyethelene powder.  the targets  used",
                " in  the  experiment  were  found  to be sufficiently",
                " homogeneous with the values N-CD = (4.415 (0.011)) *",
                " 10**21  atoms/cm**2  and  N-CH = (4.3564 (0.0086)) *",
                " 10**21 atoms/cm**2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "P"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The magnetic spectrometer with plastic",
                " scintillator detectors in its focal plane."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Magnetic spectrometers  have   been   used   in   the",
                " measurement  and  make  it  possible  to  deduce the",
                " absolute cross section  values  independent  of  the",
                " shape   of   the   spectrum   of  primary  radiation",
                " (bremsstrahlung spectrum),  and also independent  of",
                " the  calibration detailes of the conventionally used",
                " radiation monitors.  Effectively,  the ratio of  the",
                " deuteron  photodisintegration cross section into the",
                " forward direction,  to the forward direction compton",
                " electron  production  cross  section  was  measured.",
                " since the  compton  effect  cross  section  is  well",
                " known,  the photodisintegration cross section can be",
                " deduced."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
